          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><b>Hydrogen Utilization and Sustainability Act</b></p> <p>This bill expands the tax credit for producing electricity from renewable resources to include qualified hydrogen. The bill defines <em>qualified hydrogen</em> as hydrogen fuel certified as having a carbon intensity of not greater than 75 grams of CO2e (carbon dioxide equivalent) per kilowatt hour of electricity produced, as determined based on a lifecycle analysis.</p>]]>
          </text>
